âœ… 6. What is Guardian OS?
Guardian OS is the original operating system of Tandem (HPE NonStop) systems.
It is designed for high availability, fault tolerance, and real-time transaction processing.
Guardian uses a record-oriented file system (Enscribe) and supports message-based IPC between processes.
ðŸ“Œ Interview point: Guardian OS is tightly coupled with NonStop hardware for zero downtime.
